snippet.textDisplay: I am saying this not to be judgmental because I have gotten botox and won't stop getting it (until wrinkles are normalized? maybe not even then) but no one is talking about "face positivity." Ashley's forehead doesn't move. We can talk all day about bodies and that is hugely important.  But no one is talking about the "non-surgeries" people are doing to their face-- me included! We are conditioning women to believe that your face must not have a wrinkle. A forehead cannot move. Everything must be lifted. Perhaps the botox/injection conversation isn't as important nor damaging as the body conversation but why isn't it part of the conversation.

snippet.textDisplay: I knew I LOVED Demi, but even more when she speaks elaborately. Will Ferrell is a movement, I swear. Literally, I said if I ever auditioned for anything I’d watch a movie of his because he gets me in a great mood. I wish she had a talk show or a channel that she could be expressive on. The working situation and pushing through, I felt all of that. This is my first week back to work because I took 2 weeks off to gather my thoughts and allow myself clarity. I am depressed and I would have NEVER in the past taken time for me. Always staying over, filling in shifts, coming back, working two jobs and doing acting and modeling class all at one time, being in a relationship and trying to divide time for everyone and please everybody and not say NO because you want to excel and feel like you’re doing well and loved by those and appreciated by said folks, when in reality it’s taken lightly and is expected of you because you set the standard high. I now have that power to say FUCK IT and I want to be “lazy” today or that I’m not okay and I need help or time. I’m so grateful you have found that for yourself, too, Demi. We love you. We love seeing you do well and thriving, baby. “Mistakes” are life lessons and they teach you which paths to choose. So proud of you. ♥️♥️♥️😘
